Online Appointment Booking Facility: Terms of Service
Home
/ Online Appointment Booking Facility: Terms of Service
Definitions
Partners
Practo’s esteemed Partners are doctors, clinic managers, and other medical practitioners, who are listed and have a profile on
www.practo.com
and comply with the Terms of Use of
www.practo.com
.
Patients
Since it’s Practo’s mission to help mankind lead healthier and better lives, Patients are our motivation to work harder every day. Patients are defined as consumers who are seeking healthcare services from our Partners.
Practo.com
Practo.com is a web/app based platform designed/developed and owned by Practo, for our partners to offer their consultation time as appointments and for patients to book these appointments online. Availing services offered by Practo.com is subject to fulfilment of Terms of Service of Practo.com.
Online Appointments Booking Facility
Online Appointment Booking is a facility offered by Practo.com to patients for booking appointments online with our partners.
Terms of Service
Set of best practices and rules that govern the continued availability of online appointment booking facility to our partners listed on Practo.com
Objectives of Online Appointment Booking Facility
The two-fold objective of Practo.com is to ensure:
Excellent experience for our patients by minimizing their waiting time
Excellent experience for our partners by maximizing their utilization of time
Mandatory Terms of Service for Partners
Every doctor should honour all appointments booked via Practo.com.
It is mandatory that the patient meets the same doctor with whom the appointment has been confirmed.
The doctor should communicate about any expected delay/cancellation at least 2 hours prior to the scheduled time of appointment.
Non-compliance to the above will lead to poor patient experience and may attract penalties from Practo including, but not limited to, withdrawal of the ‘Book’ Privilege button and might have an adverse effect on the relevance score of the establishment on
www.practo.com. Practo reserves the right to withdraw the ‘Book’ privilege button.
Mandatory Terms of Service for Patients
‘Instant – Book Appointment’
button on Practo.com is a privilege given to the Patient, Practo reserves the right to withdraw this in case of repeated instances of “Patient No Show”.
Privileges for Partners
For complying with the terms of service on Practo.com the partners will be offered following privileges:
Online Appointments Booking Facility
Patients can seamlessly book appointments 24×7 on
practo.com
or Practo App.
Improve relevance score on Practo.com.
Practo provides the services on “as is” and “as available” basis. Practo does not represent, warrant or guarantee that your access to or use of Practo.com: (a) will be uninterrupted or error free; or (b)will result in any requests for appointments. Notwithstanding anything contained herein, Practo disclaims all liability for any act or omission of you, any Patient or other third party.
